{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κατακάμπτω</b>, <br /> <b>bend down</b>, so as to be concave, ἐξ ὀρθοῦ κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 71c; εἰς ἓν κύκλῳ [prev. work] 36b; κ. τὰς στροφάς, see at {στροφή} I.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, opposed to ἀνακάμπτομαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 386a1; φλὲψ ἐπὶ τὴν ῥάχιν -ομένη 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 15.530 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> <i>participle</i> <i>passive</i> -κεκαμμένος <b>bending over</b>, conjecture in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 3.18.8. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>cover with a vault</b>, λίθῳ κατακαμφθέντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 5.3.8. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, κ. ἐλπίδας <b>bend down, overthrow</b> hopes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 1252 (Burges, -γναψε codices, _anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be bent</b> (by entreaty), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.187. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7846","accentedUnicode":"κατακάμπτω","shortDef":"to bend down","mediumDef":"to bend down","stepGloss":"to bend down","stepTransliteration":"katakamptō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}